 Authorities are appealing to the public to help them find the vehicle. The vehicle is standard issue and is white in colour. It has light scratch marks on the back panel and the glass of the right break-light is missing. If anyone sees the vehicle, please contact members of the South African Community Crime Watch Maureen Scheepers on 082 565 6770 or Ena Pilodia on 082 415 8029 or the Middelburg police station on 013 249 1600.       Parents frustrated by a lack of space in Middelburg schools Traffic officers to appear in court for corruption #TrafficAlert: Two dead in Kranspoort accidents VIDEO: Two perish after truck jack-knifes • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za